      • joinRouteSections

        public static void joinRouteSections(RouteSection initial,
                                     RouteSection sectionToAdd)
        Attemps to append one route section to another. Will add a Discon if necessary
        Parameters:
        initial - The initial RouteSection that will be appended to.
        sectionToAdd - This RouteSection will be appended to the initial RouteSection

      • modifyRouteSectionToJoin

        public static void modifyRouteSectionToJoin(RouteSection first,
                                            RouteSection second)
        This method will check two RouteSections to check for discontinuities and ultimately prepare for the final accumulation of all legs for the path solver.
        Parameters:
        first - First RouteSection to be joined (can be null)
        second - Second RouteSection to be joined to the first one (cannot be null).

      • areLegsSuperImposed

        public static boolean areLegsSuperImposed(Leg firstLeg,
                                          Leg secondLeg)
        This method will return a boolean depending on whether two legs with different types are super imposed or not. Ex: A fix YQO can also be taken as an IF and CF but the two are at the same geographical location.
        Parameters:
        firstLeg - The first leg to use
        secondLeg - The second leg to use to check super imposition with firstLeg
        Returns:
        boolean

      • areRouteSectionsContinuous

        This method will check if two RouteSections are continuous by checking the final legs in each.
        Parameters:

        second - Second RouteSection
        Returns:
        boolean
